OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1781039474
OL,3,CUndercover investigation into
OL,4,Cunlicensed tanning products sold in
OL,5,CWales
OL,7,FIt's a Tuesday afternoon and I'm
OL,8,Fdriving from salon to salon in Wales
OL,9,Fon the hunt for unlicensed,
OL,10,Funregulated tanning products like
OL,11,Fnasal sprays and injections.
OL,13,FThey're all the craze at the moment,
OL,14,Fwith more and more people chasing a
OL,15,Fdramatic tan.
OL,17,FI've already called around to see who
OL,18,Fhas them in stock. Still, as I walk
OL,19,Finto the first salon wearing a hidden
OL,20,Fcamera, I don't quite know what to
OL,21,Fexpect.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/9
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1781039474
OL,3,CUndercover investigation into
OL,4,Cunlicensed tanning products sold in
OL,5,CWales
OL,7,F"Can I buy tanning nasal sprays,
OL,8,Fplease?", I ask.
OL,10,FI quickly realise that requests like
OL,11,Fthis must be normal here.
OL,13,FThe seller offers me three different
OL,14,Fflavours and openly admits she doesn't
OL,15,Fadvertise them because they are
OL,16,F"illegal".
OL,18,F"Loads of sun bed shops advertise
OL,19,Fthem. Like, I take them," she tells me
OL,20,Fcasually.
OL,26,@zD@AOU{D@YO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
